### Get Pods (parsed)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/pods

### Get Pods Raw (raw JSON)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/pods/raw

### Trigger Sleep Job (query param)
# Example: trigger a job that sleeps for 60s using query param
POST http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/jobs/sleep?seconds=60

### Trigger Sleep Job (JSON body)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/jobs/sleep
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "seconds": 60
}

### Save Pod Record (query params)
# Example: save a pod record via query parameters
POST http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/pods/record?name=my-pod&namespace=default&status=Running

### Save Pod Record (JSON body)
# If you prefer JSON bodies, send parameters in the body and the controller will still accept them if adapted.
POST http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/pods/record
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "my-pod",
  "namespace": "default",
  "status": "Running"
}

# cURL equivalents (examples you can run in a terminal)
# List pods (parsed):
# curl -sS http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/pods
# List pods (raw):
# curl -sS http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/pods/raw
# Trigger sleep job (query):
# curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/jobs/sleep?seconds=60"
# Trigger sleep job (json):
# curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"seconds":60}' http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/jobs/sleep
# Save pod record (query):
# curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/api/k8s/pods/record?name=my-pod&namespace=default&status=Running"